# Commit Message Template
#
# <type>(<scope>): <short summary> (max 72 chars)
#
# Types:
#   feat     — new feature
#   fix      — bug fix
#   refactor — code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   test     — adding or updating tests
#   docs     — documentation only
#   chore    — build process, dependencies, tooling
#   perf     — performance improvement
#
# Scopes (optional): pipeline, llm, worker, template, service, config, auth
#
# Short summary: imperative mood, no period at the end
#   Good: "add think-tag stripping to parseJson"
#   Bad:  "Added think-tag stripping to parseJson."
#
# Body (optional, wrap at 72 chars):
#   - Explain WHY the change is needed, not what it does
#   - Reference failing behaviour or root cause
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
